[[File:BSS - Varning till svenska flickor.jpg|thumb|Sticker from BSS warning Swedish girls not to shame their race by [[Miscegenation|having sex with]] "[[Negro|negroes]]".]] [[Image:Sdsticker.jpg|thumb|upright|140px|Early campaign sticker of the [[Sweden Democrats]] using the ''Keep Sweden Swedish'' slogan.]]'''Bevara Sverige Svenskt''' ('''BSS''', "Keep Sweden Swedish") was a [[Sweden|Swedish]] <ref name="Lodenius">[[Anna-Lena Lodenius]], [[Stieg Larsson]]: ''Extremhögern''. Tidens förlag 1991, chapter ''BSS: en folkkampanj för rasism'', {{ISBN|91-550-3686-4}}</ref><ref name="Widfeldt2015">{{cite book |last=Widfeldt |first=Anders |date=2015 |title=Extreme Right Parties in Scandinavia |url= |location= |publisher=Routledge |page= |isbn=978-0-415-26589-8 |author-link= }}</ref> movement based in [[Stockholm]] and is a slogan used by various Swedish nationalist parties. The stated objective of the BSS movement, and the aim of the slogan, was to initiate a debate in order to stop [[immigration]] by non-[[Europe]]ans and [[repatriation|repatriate]] non-ethnic Swedes. Inspiration came from the post-WW2 fascist organisation [[Nysvenska Rörelsen]] created by [[Per Engdahl]].<ref>[http://www.svd.se/nyheter/inrikes/det-fordjupar-bilden-av-kamprads-engagemang_6412096.svd SvD: ”Fördjupar bilden av Kamprads engagemang”]</ref>
Founded as a loosely organised network in 1979<ref name="Widfeldt2015"/> by [[Leif Zeilon]], and formalised as an organisation in 1983, BSS was involved with the [[Populism|populist]] [[Progress Party (Sweden)|Progress Party]] ({{lang-sv|Framstegspartiet}}) in 1986. This co-operation took place under the name [[Sweden Party]] ({{lang-sv|Sverigepartiet}}). This cooperation evolved into the [[Sweden Democrats]] ({{lang-sv|Sverigedemokraterna}}) (SD) in 1988.<ref name="Stieg">[[Stieg Larsson]] & Mikael Ekman: ''Sverigedemokraterna - Den nationella rörelsen'' {{ISBN|91-7324-877-0}}</ref>
Claiming not to be racists, their often aggressive sticker campaigns arguably indicated otherwise with [[slogan]]s such as "Låt inte din dotter bli en negerleksak" (Don't let your daughter become a [[negro]] toy) and "Negrer hotar sina offer" (Negros threaten their victims).<ref name="Lodenius"/>
Although the number of members was comparatively small, BSS represented the first organised attempt to reduce immigration and as a result received massive media attention.{{Citation needed|date=December 2009}}
The slogan "Keep Sweden Swedish" was taken on by the Sweden Democrats and became prevalent during 2003-2004, when it was used for headlines in the party newspaper "SD Kuriren" and as a slogan on bumper stickers.{{Citation needed|date=December 2009}}
