In {{NZ election link year|1893}} Massey stood as a candidate in the general election in the {{NZ electorate link|Franklin}} electorate,  losing to the [[New Zealand Liberal Party|Liberal]] candidate, [[Benjamin Harris (New Zealand politician)|Benjamin Harris]].<ref name="DNZB Massey" /> In early 1894 he was invited to contest a [[Waitemata by-election, 1894|by-election]] in the neighbouring electorate of [[Waitemata (New Zealand electorate)|Waitemata]], and was victorious. In the [[New Zealand general election, 1896|1896 election]] he stood for the [[Franklin (New Zealand electorate)|Franklin electorate]], which he represented until he died in 1925.<ref name=Scholefield>{{cite book |last= Scholefield |first= Guy |title= New Zealand Parliamentary Record, 1840–1949 |authorlink=Guy Scholefield |edition=3rd |origyear= First ed. published 1913 |year= 1950 |publisher= Govt. Printer |location= Wellington| page=126}}</ref>

